article.headline: Lafayette 84, Lycoming 73
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Sean Knitter scored 20 points -- including 18 in the second half -- to lead four Lafayette players in double figures in an 84-73 win over Lycoming on Wednesday. Lafayette (6-1) is off to its best start since 1998, when it also started 6-1. Jonathan Pribble scored 23 points to lead Lycoming (5-2). Both teams started off slow in the first half, each committing nine turnovers, and Lycoming led 29-26 at the half. Lycoming went up 42-32 with 16:05 remaining in the second after two 3-pointers from Pribble and another from Shaun Morris. But Knitter made four straight shots, including two 3-pointers, and Winston Davis had five of his 14 points to pull Lafayette closer. Rob Dill scored six straight points to give Lafayette a 58-55 lead with 7:29 left, and the Leopards went on a 10-2 run to stretch the lead to 11 with just over two minutes left. Matthew Stackhouse was 9-14 for 21 points for Lycoming. Justin DeBerry had 19 points and Dill added 12 for Lafayette.
